                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d760">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.516/222: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Beaulac</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-13T16:00:00-05:45"
                            >December 13, 1929—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:24 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>285. Department’s 171, December 9, 2 p.m. President Moncada has every pleasure at
                    your message and requests that the proposals and recommendations of the bankers
                    be transmitted to him through this Legation. He says that he has instructed his
                    representatives in Washington to cease to intervene in the matters under
                    discussion.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Beaulac</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
